'''Cheq Wong''' (Ceq Wong, Chewong) is an [[Austroasiatic languages|Austroasiatic language]] spoken in the Malay Peninsula. It belongs to the [[Jahaic languages|Northern]] subbranch of the [[Aslian languages]]. Northern Aslian was labelled Jehaic in the past.
