'''Kaj Skagen''' (born October 23, 1949 in [[Strandebarm]]) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] writer.<ref name="Ny Tid">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytid.no/arkiv/artikler/20050601/litteraturen_og_radikalismen/|title=Litteraturen og radikalismen|date=4 June 2005|work=[[Ny Tid]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref>  He received the [[Riksmål Society Literature Prize]] in 1991. His first book ''Gatedikt'' was published in 1971. From 1978 to 1989, he published and edited the periodical "Arken". In 1982 he won the first prize of a national novel contest with the novel ''Broene brenner''. In 1983 he published ''Bazarovs barn'',<ref name="Ny Tid"/> a harsh critique of contemporary Norwegian literature.

