Intermediate numbers are formed by compounding the above elements. Powers of ten are denoted by {{lang|km|រយ}} {{IPA|[rɔːj]}} (100), {{lang|km|ពាន់}} {{IPA|[pŏən]}} (1,000), {{lang|km|ម៉ឺន}} {{IPA|[məɨn]}} (10,000), {{lang|km|សែន}} {{IPA|[saen]}} (100,000), {{lang|km|លាន}} {{IPA|[liən]}} (1,000,000) and {{lang|km|កោដិ}} {{IPA|[kaot]}} (10,000,000). For more information, see [[Khmer numerals]].

[[Ordinal number]]s are formed by placing the particle {{lang|km|ទី}} {{IPA|[tiː]}} before the corresponding cardinal number.

==Demonstratives==
In Khmer, demonstratives follow the nouns that they modify. In standard literary Khmer, there are two degrees of distance, but there are other distinctions in colloquial language. Demonstratives can also function as articles only after introductory clauses.

