{{distinguish|Mangbetu language}} {{Infobox language |name=Mangbutu |region=[[Democratic Republic of Congo|Congo (DRC)]] |speakers=15,000 |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=Eastern |fam4=[[Mangbutu–Lese languages|Mangbutu–Lese]] |iso3=mdk |glotto=mang1396 |glottorefname=Mangbutu }} '''Mangbutu''' is a [[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic language]] of northeastern [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congo]]. It, or its speakers, are also known as ''Mangu-Ngutu, Mombuttu, Wambutu.'' The 1,200 Andinai are separated from other Mangbutu speakers by [[Lese language|Lese]]; they speak a distinct dialect, as do the Andali tribe (Angwe dialect).
